p: Our simulated AGB ranges from 11 to 57% higher than that modeled by Hudiburg ( Table 3). AGD carbon also ranges from 79 to 105% higher, and AGT carbon ranges from 28 to 68% higher. Among our simulations, AGB, AGD, and AGT are highest for NF-WCE, and lowest for SF-WCE ( Table 3). AGB, AGD, and AGT densities are generally higher and more flatly distributed than Hudiburgâ€™s ( Fig 5). AGB, AGD, and AGT density distributions are flattest for SF-WCE.
